    "created_at": "2018-05-18T08:58:32Z",
    "updated_at": "2018-05-18T08:58:32Z",
    "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
    "body": "> Or is there some reason why not to do this?\r\n\r\nIf an approximate simulation is acceptable then some code could be added to Pandas to do it for the openlyxl and xlsxwriter engines. There aren't any technical issue. There are some other things to consider however:\r\n\r\n- Someone needs to do the work.\r\n- The solution will only be approximate. There will be cases where it  doesn't work as expected and users will complain.\r\n\r\n"
