    "updated_at": "2018-05-19T12:39:02Z",
    "author_association": "NONE",
    "body": "I think that will be acceptable (I guess it is the same that StyleFrame does and the best possible way of achieving it from within pandas).\r\n\r\n> Someone needs to do the work.\r\n\r\nAgreed, probably the main problem. However I guess most of the code from StyleFrame can get reused. Still I think then it is worth to either reopen this issue or create a new one, so someone who is interested can do it.\r\n\r\n> The solution will only be approximate. There will be cases where it doesn't work as expected and users will complain.\r\n\r\nI am unaware of how good StyleFrame or others currently do it. However I assume they do it pretty well so one does not notice a big difference from the Excel integrated auto-adjust."
